main event: An unidentified object resembling a falling star was observed over Germany on 9 March 1955.
interesting points: The object was round and orange, emitting no sound,The sighting lasted for approximately 15 seconds,The estimated speed of the object was between 300-400 mph,The observer noted the object had an altitude of approximately 1500-2000 ft, Similar reports from the area suggest consistency in the type of sightings.
sighted object: round orange object in the sky
witness description: LT Paul A McGuay from the 74 Fighter Interceptor Squadron
